1. Install virtualenv:
	sudo pip3 install virtualenv

2. mkdir Django_project
3. cd Django_project
4. virtualenv -p python3 newenv2
5. Activate virtual env: source newenv/bin/activate
6. Deactivate: deactivate
7. cd newenv
8. pip3 install django
	

9. Create project Backend
	django-admin startproject Backend

10. cd Backend
11. python manage.py startapp backend_app

12. Create models & generate migration files by:
		python manage.py makemigrations	

	Run migration files by:
		python manage.py migrate

13. Install sqlitebrowser for testing:
		sudo add-apt-repository -y ppa:linuxgndu/sqlitebrowser
		sudo apt-get update
		sudo apt-get install sqlitebrowser

14. To let admin access and edit the entries in Models:
		i. django manage.py createsuperuser
		ii. python manage.py startserver
		iii. Go to URL/admin and login 	

15. Open django shell:
		python manage.py shell

16. Install MySql:
	Follow this: https://www.digitalocean.com/community/tutorials/how-to-use-mysql-or-mariadb-with-your-django-application-on-ubuntu-14-04

	sudo apt-get update

	sudo apt-get install python-pip python-dev mysql-server libmysqlclient-dev

	sudo mysql_install_db

	sudo mysql_secure_installation

	mysql -u root -p

	CREATE DATABASE judge_database;	

	CREATE USER judge_user@localhost IDENTIFIED BY 'password';

	FLUSH PRIVILEGES;

	exit

17. Install mysqlclient package for django:
	source newenv/bin/activate
	pip install django mysqlclient
